# Local Testing Fallbacks

RUN.game SDK features are unavailable when running locally (localhost). Always provide fallbacks.

## SDK Features That Don't Work Locally

- `RundotGameAPI.globalStorage` — cross-game shared storage (e.g. RUN TV watch status)
- `RundotGameAPI.appStorage` — uses `safeStorage.ts` wrappers which handle this
- `RundotGameAPI.ads` — ad calls will fail silently
- `RundotGameAPI.context.shareParams` — no deep link data
- Registration / add-to-home / entitlements — platform-only

## Fallback Pattern

```typescript
// Always try SDK first, fall back to localStorage for local dev
try {
  const val = await RundotGameAPI.globalStorage.getItem('key');
  if (val === '1') { unlock(); return; }
} catch { /* SDK unavailable */ }

// localStorage fallback for local testing
try {
  if (localStorage.getItem('key') === '1') { unlock(); }
} catch { /* noop */ }
```

## Debug Mode

The debug panel (class select screen, `?debug` URL param or 5-tap subtitle) provides manual toggles for SDK-gated features. When adding new SDK-gated unlocks, add a corresponding debug toggle.
